Let $a^2+b^2=0$ and $(a,b)\neq (0,0)$. Let $\mathbf{a}_i=ae_1+be_2+\cdots+ae_{2i-1}+be_{2i}$, for $i=1,\ldots,[\frac{n}{2}]$. Let $W$ be the vector subspace generated by $\{ \mathbf{a}_i\mid i=1,\ldots,[\frac{n}{2}] \}$. Then $W-\{ \mathbf{0} \}$ is a clique in $TD(\mathbb{F},n)$ of size $|\mathbb{F}|^{[\frac{n}{2}]}-1$.

If $n$ is odd, then $W \cup \{ e_{n} \}$ is a clique set. Hence, $\omega(TD(\mathbb{F},n))\geq |\mathbb{F}|^{[\frac{n}{2}]}$.
\end{proof}
